data.value:
When typing english to translate, avoid using words with suffixes, just use the base word.
Long vowel sounds are double letters, otherwise letters are not duplicated or doubled. Words are spelled as they sound.
True sounds: • C = CH sound, never used as K or S sound. • F = F && PH sound. PH is never used, use F instead. • K = K sound, own unique sound. • Q = Qu sound. • S = S sound, own unique sound. • New letter: SH = used as SH sound. English letters S+H are made into one letter. • New letter: TH = used as TH sound. English letters T+H are made into one letter. • G = Hard G, never J sound, and vise versa. • Y = A y by itself makes an e` sound, which is also the word: and.
Structure: • Subject first, then describe subject. Similar to American Sign Language. • Most words will not have more than one synonym; they will use the primary words.
*Bottom textbox shows how to pronounce it.
